layName":"Matt Clark","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"updated":"2013-08-19T16:32:35.311-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/11300","id":"11300","name":"QA","description":"Bugs/Tasks associated with the QA team"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"Running a test which launches an image with at least 1 empty ebs block device, once the image goes to running state some amount of unique data is written with dd into the block device and the same amount is read back in to create an md5 checksum to associate with the volume. \r\nWhen the instance is stop -> started the device and volume are present but the data is lost. \r\nWe manually verified by formatting the disk, and creating a file and writing to it. The file was lost after stop -> start. \r\nIt appears that not all volumes lose their data after stop->start. Current 'guess' is that the NC thinks this is ephemeral and is possibly formatting, writing, mounting the drive?\r\nThanks,\r\n-Matt","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"Data lost on mapped block device after stop/start","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=mclark","name":"mclark","key":"mclark","accountId":"557058:9b68e4d6-90d8-47d3-9c86-519770009164","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-